<h1>Faraja Lutula Msemwa</h1>
<p class="intro">Tanzania</p>

<img src="/images/training/large/msemwa.jpg" alt="" class="bio-photo">

<p>Dr. Faraja L. Msemwa is an Emergency Preparedness and Response Officer for the Tanzania Ministry Of Health. She has worked in public health and emergency management for over 8 years. She supported the Joint External Evaluation and development of National Action Plan for Health Security for both Tanzania Mainland and Zanzibar.</p>
<p>In her current roles she coordinates preparedness and response activities including training of rapid response teams and other emergency response teams, simulation exercises, and development of emergency preparedness plans.</p>
<p>Dr. Msemwa is a member of National IHR technical working group and Ministry of Health Focal Point for One Health. She is a holder of Medical Degree, Masters of Public health and Masters of Disaster Management.</p>

<h3>Quote</h3>
<blockquote>&ldquo;Preparedness for public health emergencies including epidemic outbreaks is my great passion and area of interest. When I work in preparedness it always brings positive results coming from the impact of the particular strengthened capacity.&rdquo;</blockquote>

